nditions $k_f$, and time. But the influence disappears as time passes\n($\\sim e^{-\\eta k_f^2 t}$), so the saturated magnetic fields are independent of\nthe initial conditions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 29 May 2014 05:22:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-09-22"}
